    <h2 style="font-size: 35px; font-weight: bold; color: black;">2.0 Mug-Share Users</h2>
    <p style="text-align:justify">
        The Mug-Share Users web page is used to manage the Mug-Share Users data table in the database.
        Users can be added individually and through an excel upload, once created, user profiles can be viewed, edited, and deleted.
        The search bar on the top right can be used to find a record based on UBC ID, first name, last name, or total mugs borrowed.
        <br />
        <br />
        Access this page by clicking the ‘Mug-Share Users’ tab on the navbar at the top of any page (aside from the login screen).
    </p>

    <h3 id="2.1" style="font-weight: bold; color: black;">2.1 How to Add a New User to the Program</h3>
    <p style="text-align:justify">
        <ol style="margin-left: 2em;">
            <li>Click the green ‘Create New’ button above the top left of the data table to open a modal window.</li>
            <li>
                Fill out the user’s information, while keeping in mind the following rules:
                <ul>
                    <li>UBC ID - must be a 7 or 8 digit number that does not already exist in the database</li>
                    <li>Email - must not already exist in the database</li>
                    <li>Notes - this field may remain empty and is used for storing any special notes</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Once the all the required fields are filled out, click the blue ‘Save’ button to add the new user record to the database.</li>
        </ol>
        *Note: the ‘Cancel’ button or ‘X’ button in the top right can be pressed at anytime to close the modal.
    </p>

    <h3 id="2.2" style="font-weight: bold; color: black;">2.2 How to Upload a List of User Records From an Excel Document</h3>
    <p style="text-align:justify">
        <ol style="margin-left: 2em;">
            <li>Click the blue ‘Upload From Excel’ button above the top left of the data table to open a modal window.</li>
            <li>Click the ‘Browse’ button next to the textbox to open a file explorer window.</li>
            <li>Find the ‘.xls’ file containing the user records you wish to upload. Ensure that the format of the excel file is ‘.xls’ as ‘.csv’ and ‘.xlsx’ files will not work.</li>
            <li>Click the ‘Submit’ button once you have found the file you wish to upload.</li>
            <li>
                A warning modal will appear to warn you that all the existing user records in the database will be deleted and replaced with the data from excel.
                Before proceeding with the upload, it is advised that you record all information for users who are still associated with rented mugs,
                and/or have rented the most mugs during the previous session.
            </li>
        </ol>
        *Note: the ‘Cancel’ button or ‘X’ button in the top right can be pressed at anytime to close the modal.
    </p>

    <h3 id="2.3" style="font-weight: bold; color: black;">2.3 How to View a User’s Profile</h3>
    <p style="text-align:justify">
        <ol style="margin-left: 2em;">
            <li>Locate the user record you wish to view, and click the blue ‘View’ button in the far right column of the data table to open a modal containing that user’s information.</li>
            <li>Click the ‘Close’ button or ‘X’ button in the top right when you are done viewing the user’s record in order to close the modal.</li>
        </ol>
    </p>

    <h3 id="2.4" style="font-weight: bold; color: black;">2.4 How to Edit a User’s Profile</h3>
    <p style="text-align:justify">
        <ol style="margin-left: 2em;">
            <li>Locate the user record you wish to edit and click the blue ‘Edit’ button in the far right column of the data table to open a modal containing that user’s information.</li>
            <li>
                Update any of the fields as needed, while keeping in mind the following rules:
                <ul>
                    <li>UBC ID - must be a 7 or 8 digit number that does not already exist in the database</li>
                    <li>Email - must not already exist in the database</li>
                    <li>
                        Mug In Use - if unchecking the box to clear a user’s rental status, the ‘Date of Rental’ field must be cleared.
                        If checking the box to say a user is currently in possession of a mug, the ‘Date of Rental’ field must be filled in with a date
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Date of Rental - field must be empty if the ‘Mug In Use’ box is unchecked, otherwise it must be filled in with a date (eg. YYYY/MM/DD or YYYY-MM-DD)
                    </li>
                    <li>Notes - this field may remain empty and is used for storing any special notes</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                If any changes are made to the record that you wish to upload to the database, press the blue ‘Save Changes’ button at the bottom of the modal
                to update the record in the database.
            </li>
        </ol>
        *Note: the ‘Cancel’ button or ‘X’ button in the top right can be pressed at anytime to close the modal.
    </p>

    <h3 id="2.5" style="font-weight: bold; color: black;">2.5 How to Remove a User From the Program</h3>
    <p style="text-align:justify">
        <ol style="margin-left: 2em;">
            <li>Locate the user record you wish to delete and click the red ‘Delete button in the far right column of the data table to open a modal containing that user’s information.</li>
            <li>
                If you wish to proceed with deleting this record, press the blue ‘Delete Record’ button. However, note that once a record is deleted, the action cannot be undone,
                unless a backup of the database exists, in which case follow the instructions on the troubleshooting document.
            </li>
        </ol>
        *Note: the ‘Cancel’ button or ‘X’ button in the top right can be pressed at anytime to close the modal.
    </p>

