                        Update any of the fields as needed, while keeping in mind the following rules:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Staff Card ID - must be a 7 or 8 digit number that does not already exist in the database</li>
                            <li>Username - cannot contain spaces, and must not already exist in the database</li>
                            <li>Email - must not already exist in the database</li>
                            <li>Admin Permission - check this box if you want the staff user to have the ability to delete data and access the Security, and Email List pages</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If any changes are made to the record that you wish to upload to the database, press the blue
                        ‘Save Changes’ button at the bottom of the modal to update the record in the database.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                *Note: the ‘Cancel’ button or ‘X’ button in the top right can be pressed at anytime to close the modal.
            </p>

            <h3 id="7.4" style="font-weight: bold; color: black;">7.4 How to Remove a Staff User From the Program</h3>
            <p style="text-align:justify">
                <ol style="margin-left: 2em;">
                    <li>Locate the staff user record you wish to delete and click the red ‘Delete button in the far right column of the data table to open a modal containing that staff user’s information.</li>
                    <li>
                        If you wish to proceed with deleting this record, press the blue ‘Delete Record’ button. However, note that once a record is deleted,
                        the action cannot be undone, unless a backup of the database exists, in which case follow the instructions on the troubleshooting document.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                *Note: the ‘Cancel’ button or ‘X’ button in the top right can be pressed at anytime to close the modal.
            </p>

